  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Water, sanitation, and hygiene response to floods in the La Mojana region</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The main objective of this project is to provide life-saving WASH assistance to vulnerable communities affected by flooding. This UNICEF project provides fresh water to flood-affected households, builds latrines, and provides hygiene kits. The project provides life-saving assistance to 7,000 people, including 2,511 women, 2,297 men, 2,192 children, and 310 persons with disabilities.</narrative>
  </description>
